Problem:
class ProductDatabase {
  private List<Product> products = new ArrayList<>();

  public void addProduct(Product product) {
    this.products.add(product);
  }

  public boolean searchProductByName(String name) {
    for (Product product : products) {
      if (product.getName().equals(name)) {
        return true;
      }
    }
    return false;
  }

  public void removeProductByName(String name) {
    this.products.removeIf(product -> product.getName().equals(name));
  }

  public void applyDiscount(String categoryName, double discountRate) {
    for (Product product : products) {
      if (product.getCategory().equals(categoryName)) {
        double newPrice = product.getPrice() * (1 - discountRate);
        product.setPrice(newPrice);
      }
    }
  }
}",

If applying a discount results in an increase in the number of product removals, can we infer that higher prices were preventing removals?
